-- Central Bank Sells 3-Month Bills at Unchanged 1.5704% Yield, Traders Say
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-22T02:05:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-22/central-bank-sells-3-month-bills-at-unchanged-1-5704-yield-traders-say.html

          
          
             The Peopleâ€™s Bank of China sold
three-month bills at a yield of 1.5704 percent in open-market
operations, unchanged for a fourth straight sale, according to
traders at China Citic Bank Corp. and Bank of Shanghai Co.  
 The monetary authority, which offered 80 billion yuan
($11.8 billion) of the 91-day notes, has let the yield rise at
five previous auctions this year. The rate last climbed four
basis points, or 0.04 percentage point, to 1.5704 percent on
June 10.  
